Remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} from the fridge to bring them up to room temperature. Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the potato on a large #baking tray{} and drizzle with @olive oil{1}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Thinly slice half the @green chilli{1/2}. Finely chop the rest. Halve the @corn on the cob{2} by running a #knife{} firmly around the middle then snapping in half with your hands.

Put the corn on the cob on a large sheet of #foil{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Put the chilli slices and half the @garlic clove{1} (keep the clove whole with the skin on) on top then scrunch the foil closed to create a parcel. Put this on the tray alongside the sweet potato. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until the sweet potato are soft and golden and the corn is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn the potato halfway.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the remaining @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} and the @coriander{1} (stalks and all). Put the grated garlic, chopped chilli and herbs in a #bowl{} along with the @cider vinegar{15}ml, @olive oil{} and @sugar{1}. Stir together then season to taste with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Set aside - this is your chimichurri dressing!

When the potatoes and corn have about 15 mins left, put a #frying pan{} on high heat with a drizzle of oil. Season the steaks with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. When the oil is hot, carefully lay the steaks in the pan and brown for ~{1%minute} on each side. Once browned, lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side.

> TIP: This will cook the steak to medium rare - if you like yours less rare just cook for 1-2 mins more.

As soon as the steaks are cooked to your liking, transfer to a clean #plate{} and spread the @BBQ sauce{32} all over both sides. Loosely cover with foil and leave to rest for a few mins - this will help the steak get nice and juicy.

Divide the sweet potato and corn between your plates. Slice the steaks and lay alongside, making sure your drizzle over the BBQ-y juices! Finish by spooning the chimichurri dressing all over. Enjoy!